#file manager : thunar
sudo apt install thunar
How to make it default go to menu type default application and select it.
App lancher Going to use rofi 
You can either install it from git hub or with the pacmanager apt
https://github.com/davatorium/rofi
to run rofi use: rofi -show run 
and to select a theme you can do rofi-theme-selector
the  themes are in /usr/share/rofi/themes
The one I use is dracula theme from this rofi collection:
https://github.com/Murzchnvok/rofi-collection 
to add it as a shortcut use:
Keyboards - add new shortcut name: rofi command: rofi -show run -theme ~/rofi-collection/dracula/dracula.rasi 
